CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 24, 1962, pg. A16 reads: "Scores of Elks from all corners of the Keystone State converged in Pittsburghs' Penn-Sheraton Hotel, last Friday, to pay tribute to Grand Exalted Ruler, Hobson R. Reynolds...The event was the second annual Inaugural Ball, honoring Elkdom's highest official."
TitMainTitle: Group of two women, and eight men wearing dark suits, two wearing fez and chain collars, including Hobson R. Reynolds wearing  fez with large tassel, walking in hallway of the Penn Sheraton, for Elks Second Annual Inaugural Ball, with three men wearing military uniforms in foreground
